# Rescoping Playbook

A short, mirrored version of this lives as a **user-level rule** ("ACCAdminsuite rescoping playbook") so it's available automatically in any brand-new repo without needing to be copied in. Keep both in sync when you learn something new — update the user-level rule for process/checklist changes, and add a new case-study entry below for project-specific specifics.

## Why this exists

ACCAdminsuite's core (offline-first, single-file, `.accdata`, IndexedDB blob storage, local launcher bridge, Outlook-sync ingestion, save/load, audit log, theme/UI kit) is proven and hospital-approved. Repeating coworkers/roles (a different admin, the boss, etc.) need narrower tools that share this DNA but cut irrelevant modules and add role-specific ones. Don't rebuild the plumbing each time; don't force every role into one bloated app either.

## Process

1. **Capture the job scope as a conversation, not a spec.** Let the coworker describe their day-to-day in their own words (chasing things up, billing, what triggers each step, what they email/receive). Don't ask them to fill in a schema up front.
2. **Parse notes into a draft plan yourself; fill gaps from what ACCAdminsuite already solved.** Only surface true open questions back to the requester — things that would change the shape of the plan, not every field. State your assumptions and defaults explicitly so they're easy to correct.
3. **Decide the reuse strategy** (ask if genuinely ambiguous, otherwise default):
   - **Default: new standalone repo**, scaffolded by copying/forking reusable pieces from ACCAdminsuite (see building blocks below). Each persona gets an independently deployable, independently versioned app — safest, matches "we'll do this a few more times."
   - Only propose extracting a **shared core library** once there are 3+ forked suites and a clear, stable common surface — premature abstraction before that point costs more than it saves.
   - Adding a module to the *existing* ACCAdminsuite repo is rarely right when the persona's job scope is meaningfully different (couples unrelated products, mixes unrelated users' data/concerns).
4. **Map the new domain onto existing primitives** before inventing new ones. Common translations:
   - Any "thing tracked per person" → `Patient`-like record + a domain entity (`Claim`, `EquipmentLoan`, etc.) referencing it by id.
   - Any "editable rates/prices the org updates over time" → the `serviceRates: Record<Code, number>` pattern in `Settings` (see [src/types/index.ts](/Users/prakritichhetri/ACCAdminsuite/src/types/index.ts)) — one editable table, versionless, no fixed reset default.
   - Any "attach a file to a record" → `ClaimDocument`-style metadata row + IndexedDB blob store, never bytes in the main autosaved blob (see [src/lib/idb.ts](/Users/prakritichhetri/ACCAdminsuite/src/lib/idb.ts), [src/lib/letterCache.ts](/Users/prakritichhetri/ACCAdminsuite/src/lib/letterCache.ts)).
   - Any "multi-step status per record" → a small ordered stage enum + a visual step-tracker component, denormalized onto the record for fast list rendering (avoid recomputing status from history on every render).
   - Any "emails start/drive the process" → the staging/Review Queue pattern ([src/lib/staging.ts](/Users/prakritichhetri/ACCAdminsuite/src/lib/staging.ts), [src/modules/ReviewQueue.tsx](/Users/prakritichhetri/ACCAdminsuite/src/modules/ReviewQueue.tsx)): land in a queue for one-button accept-into-record, full email history kept per record afterward. Reuse the Outlook-sync + local launcher bridge for automated ingestion once the manual flow is validated — don't port the PowerShell bridge on day one of a new repo.
   - Any "generate/track a specific known form" (e.g. ACC4249 loan form) → treat as a document kind + a tracked progress stage first; only build bespoke parsing/extraction once you have a real sample of the form and see it recurring.
5. **Build order:** data model → core record CRUD module → domain-specific centerpiece feature (the thing that makes this persona's job easier day one) → secondary features → polish/UI passes. Don't front-load polish.
6. **Cut aggressively.** Anything specific to the *other* persona's workflow (e.g. nursing service-code billing, compliance rules, complex-case tracking) should not exist in the new repo at all, not just be hidden in the UI.
7. **After shipping, log a case study below** so the next rescoping (next coworker, or the boss) starts from real examples instead of a blank playbook.

## Building blocks worth reusing as-is (from ACCAdminsuite)

- Persistence: `src/lib/idb.ts` (IndexedDB stores, blob storage, recent-files), `src/state/store.ts` (Zustand store, autosave, save-into-file-handle, rollback-on-commit-failure pattern).
- File handling: `src/lib/fileSniff.ts` (byte-level type detection), `src/components/PdfPreview.tsx` (offline preview + text fallback), `src/lib/letterCache.ts` (MIME inference, blob/parse caching).
- UI shell: `src/components/TopBar.tsx`, `src/components/Sidebar.tsx`, `src/lib/theme.ts`, `src/index.css` (theme tokens, density modes).
- Ingestion pipeline (only once manual flow is proven): `scripts/launcher/*.ps1` (local bridge, Outlook COM sync, folder watch), `src/lib/localAccBridge.ts`, `src/lib/staging.ts`, `src/modules/ReviewQueue.tsx`.
- Build/verify tooling: `scripts/verify-build.mjs` (CSP checks — keep `connect-src 'self'` for the local bridge, `'wasm-unsafe-eval'` if OCR is needed), `scripts/copy-launcher.mjs`.

## Case studies

### 1. Loan Equipment Tracker (coworker, started 2026-07-11)

- **Persona:** Coworker with similar role to the primary user, but scoped to hospital loan equipment (not nursing service billing).
- **Job scope (coworker's own words):** track patient info useful for chasing up loan equipment and billing; know where each patient is in the process and who needs following up/re-emailing; maintain an editable equipment price list; save the initial patient email plus all subsequent emails as attachments under each patient for full history; a visual progress tracker per patient; the ACC4249 loan form is the essential first step many patients skip.
- **Reuse strategy chosen:** new standalone repo, forked from ACCAdminsuite, reusing persistence/UI/file-handling building blocks above; email ingestion starts manual (attach email/attachment per patient), Outlook-sync/launcher bridge ported later once validated.
- **Kept:** `Patient` record shape (id/name/nhi/dob/notes), IndexedDB blob + document metadata pattern, editable-rates-table pattern (repurposed as the price list), save/load `.accdata`, audit log, theme/UI kit.
- **Cut:** `ServiceLine`/`ServiceCode` package calculator, `Approval` (NS04/NS05), `Billing`/`InvoiceLine` nursing-specific flow, `ComplexCases`, `Declines`, `Compliance` module, `ImportedTables`.
- **New:** `EquipmentLoan`/loan-case entity per patient, `PriceListItem` catalog, ordered progress-stage enum + step-tracker UI, per-patient email/attachment history view, ACC4249 tracked as a document-kind + stage (bespoke parsing deferred — no sample form captured yet).
- **Open questions logged for follow-up:** exact ordered list of progress stages (drafted from the one sample follow-up email + "loan form is step one", needs coworker confirmation); billing model for equipment (flat fee vs. per-item price vs. daily rate); whether billing target is ACC or the DHB; whether the Outlook-sync bridge should be pointed at the coworker's own mailbox/shared inbox and on what timeline.
- **Lessons for next time:** ask for the actual sample form/attachment up front rather than assuming it's included with an email; the "cut down current suite" framing usually means a fully separate persona-specific product, not an added module for someone who also needs the original features.

### 2. Manager Remittance / Task Tracker (Amy, the manager — started 2026-07-12)

- **Persona:** Amy May, the team manager. Oversees invoicing across ~25 ACC contracts owned by different team members; wants to reconcile ACC remittances against invoices and delegate the held/declined lines to whoever owns each contract, then track progress. SHARED across manager + team (multi-user), not single-user. Repo: `/Users/prakritichhetri/ACC-RemittanceTracker`.
- **Job scope (own words):** dashboard of invoicing across all contracts; upload invoicing + remittances; cross-check them, drop already-paid patients (or note paid), surface still-held ones with the reason code; send review items to the team member responsible for the contract; track task progress. Explicitly NOT a monthly-billing entry tool.
- **Reuse strategy:** new standalone repo **forked from ACC-LoanEquipmentTracker** (nearest sibling, leaner shell than ACCAdminsuite). Stripped all loan/equipment/email/monitoring/PDF/OCR code.
- **Kept:** offline-first `.accdata` + IndexedDB persistence, Zustand store skeleton (autosave, lock/idle, recovery, recent files, ZIP backup), theme/UI kit, `AssumptionBanner`, launcher loopback server + `verify-build`/`copy-launcher`, the "raw upload blob + metadata row + re-parse/backfill" pattern.
- **Cut:** `Patient`/`EquipmentLoan`, price list, all email/staging/Outlook-COM ingestion, PDF preview + Tesseract OCR (+ their deps and the CSP `wasm-unsafe-eval`/`blob:` directives), monitoring import.
- **New:** `Contract`/`TeamMember`(role manager|staff)/`InvoiceBatch`+`InvoiceLine`/`RemittanceBatch`+`RemittanceLine`/`ReviewTask`(+append-only `TaskNote[]`)/`SourceFileMeta`, all with `updatedAt`/`updatedBy`; seed catalogue from the real annual-billing workbook tabs (stable `contract_<slug>` ids, expired = inactive); CSV importers grounded in real samples; `REASON_CODES` lookup; pure `reconcile.ts` + a `reconcileData` store step that auto-creates one review task per held line, auto-assigned to the contract owner and preserving human edits across re-parse; Dashboard/Invoices/Remittances/Review Queue/My Tasks/Contracts/Team/Settings modules; one generic `DismissableAssumption` for all banners; **shared-folder sync** (`src/lib/sync.ts` LWW-per-record merge + notes union; launcher extended with opt-in `sync-config.json` + `/_acc/sync` + `/_acc/sync/status`). Browser only calls its own loopback bridge (keeps `connect-src 'self'`); the launcher merges the incoming payload with a SINGLE shared state file on the network drive (I:) that every machine points at — no host PC, no TCP listener, no port, no firewall rule, just the same watch-a-shared-location file-share I/O as the sibling suites' folder-watch. Sync config/state are git-ignored (PHI).
- **Critical data finding:** the invoice `ClaimNumber` matches the remittance **`ACC45 Ref`** column, NOT the long numeric `ACC Claim Number`; client names disagree between the two files for the same claim — so matching is claim-only, names are display-only. Deterministic per-batch line ids keep review tasks linked across re-parse.
- **Lessons for next time:** fork from the nearest sibling suite, not always ACCAdminsuite; when a whole capability is deleted (PDF/OCR), also tighten the CSP and drop the now-unused deps + build steps + their `verify-build` assertions or the build breaks; `launch.ps1` must stay ASCII-only (no em-dashes — `copy-launcher.mjs` asserts it); a partial `node_modules` from a repo copy can leave dev packages missing their `dist/` (clean reinstall fixes it); for multi-user-on-a-network-drive, DEFAULT TO a shared-file merge (every machine reads/merges/writes the SAME file on the drive, atomically via temp-then-move) over a host+LAN-listener design — a hospital network will reliably let you read/write a mapped drive but may well block a new inbound port, and the shared-file design is also simpler (no host/client asymmetry) and reuses a pattern (watch a shared location) already proven by the sibling suites' folder-watch. The explicit LWW+notes-union merge itself (not the transport) is what's worth keeping — it's simpler/more testable than a CRDT and transport-agnostic, so this pivot only touched the launcher + Settings + a couple of type names, not the merge logic.
